f, g \in A
 \gamma'(0)(fg) = \lim_{t \to 0} { \gamma_t(fg) - fg \over t} = \lim_{t \to 0} { \gamma_t f \gamma_t g - \gamma_t f \cdot g + \gamma_t f \cdot g - fg \over t} 
 = \lim_{t \to 0} {\gamma_t f (\gamma_t g - g) \over t} + \lim_{t \to 0} g{(\gamma_t f - f) \over t} 
 = f \gamma'(0)(g) + g \gamma'(0)(f). 
